article.headline: Army 83, Lafayette 65
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Jarell Brown scored 25 points to lead Army in an 83-65 win over Lafayette Wednesday. Matt Bell added 24 for Army (14-14, 4-9 Patriot League). Andrew Brown scored 19 to lead Lafayette (9-19, 3-10). Army shot 71.4 percent from the floor in the first half in jumping out to a 22-point lead less than 14 minutes into the game. The Black Knights reeled off a 25-8 scoring spurt to assume a commanding 39-17 advantage with less than seven minutes to play before halftime. Lafayette outscored Army 21-8 to cut their lead to nine points (47-38) at intermission. The Black Knights finished with a 60.5 percent shooting average, while Lafayette shot at 31.9 percent. Army outrebounded Lafayette 32-23.
